      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Yeah, mocking final classes requires heavier machinery. Mockito usually dismisses such problems, saying the design is to blame. For this, look at Powermock: <a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/powermock/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">code.google.com/p/powermock</a>. It can mock pretty much everything: final classes, statics, <code>new</code> calls etc. I&#39;ve never heard of mocking field access, though. Yet another reason to use getters. As for mocking primitives... they don&#39;t have behaviour, what would you like to achieve?"
