    "answer_id" : 18532604,
    "question_id" : 18532512,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"https://site.mockito.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Mockito</a> and <a href=\"https://site.mockito.org/javadoc/current/org/mockito/Mockito.html#RETURNS_DEEP_STUBS\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">RETURNS_DEEP_STUBS</a> option might be what you're looking for. What's more, mockito seems often to return sensible values by default.</p>\n<p>Example usage from the linked documentation, for quick reference:</p>\n<pre><code>Foo mock = mock(Foo.class, RETURNS_DEEP_STUBS);\n\n// note that we're stubbing a chain of methods here: getBar().getName()\nwhen(mock.getBar().getName()).thenReturn(&quot;deep&quot;);\n\n// note that we're chaining method calls: getBar().getName()\nassertEquals(&quot;deep&quot;, mock.getBar().getName());\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
